Text.SourceString: What do you want?//I’ve got no business with you.
Are you always this chatty?
People sure like to garden here. Tch.
I’d set all the animals at the shelter free if I could.
Lots of people here, like my aunt, grow their own food.//There’s a small garden in front of the guild too…<NpcName>Kira’s</>.
I’d set all the animals at the shelter free if I could. But it wouldn’t be safe for them.//They don’t know how to live in the wild.
I don’t go to the cavern.//I don’t have any reason to since I don’t mine or collect artifacts.
So you came here from Pokyo, huh?
Pokyo has a real problem with strays. Their shelters are overcrowded.
What are you doing here on a Thursday?
Can you believe this heat? I’ve never sweat so much in my life.
People here seem to like Spring weather.//They’re so annoyingly vocal about it.
I could use some homemade tomato soup.
Kinda nice to see you out in this harsh weather.//<portrait=normal>Doesn’t seem like it bothers you, huh?//Nice…nice.
The birds are back.
The birds are back.//It’s nice to walk outside with them around again.
It would be better if it were Winter all year round. Maybe I should move farther north.
Need to put out more water for the animals.
This? Hot?//<portrait=normal>No, it isn’t. Stop complaining.
This? Hot?//<portrait=normal>Maybe it’s a bit hot, but nothing unbearable.
Breathe that Winter air in, Garden Rake.//It’ll toughen you up.
Breathe that Winter air in, <PlayerName>$player</>.//It’ll toughen you up.
I don’t have any weapons at home, no. Why?
I don’t have any weapons at home, no.//I have a niece with me, <NPCName>Zoe</>. I don’t want any accidents or anything like that.
Caught someone slipping in the rain the other day…wearing sandals. Tch.//And he wondered why he slipped.
You need a pair of nice, sturdy boots for walking in the rain.//My boots have saved me from slipping many times.
I don’t like fishing.//And I also don’t like being interrupted.
Fishing isn’t my thing. I could if I had to, of course.//<portrait=annoyed>What type of person couldn’t fish or make their own food?
The hot spring is free. I wonder why more people don’t go there.
It’s safe here in Fall. It isn’t too hot.//In some places, this is wildfire season.//I’ve run away from several of those myself.
Favorite season? I don’t have one.//All seasons are the same.
Favorite season? I don’t have one.//All seasons are the same. We make too much fuss about them.//The temperature changes… No big deal.
Why are you talking to me here, in the middle of the rain?//What’s so important, Garden Rake?
Why are you talking to me here, in the middle of the storm?//What’s so important, Garden Rake?
Why are you still here?
Stop looking at my face. It’s still the same. Nothing’s changed.
The scar on my face? It doesn’t hurt anymore.//<portrait=angry>Any other questions?
The scar on my face? It doesn’t hurt anymore.//<portrait=normal>Do you think I’d be less miserable if I’d never gotten attacked?//I don’t think so.
You’re adventurous, aren’t you, Garden Rake?
What? You don’t like the nickname?
Heh heh!//[His chuckles sound like an earthquake.]
Ha! Easy on the compliments. We just met. You don’t really know me yet.//<portrait=annoyed>Easily impressed, are you?
Sorry if I call you “Garden Rake.” It’s a reference to the first time we– tch. Never mind.//<portrait=angry>If you don’t like the nickname, that’s too bad, ’cause it’ll happen again.
Those monsters were sure agitated today…//Eavesdropping on me, Garden Rake?
No, I can’t go with you to the cavern.
Watch out if you’re headed into the cavern today. <Italic>They</> seem agitated.
No, I can’t go with you to the cavern.//I have important things to do.
Your hair is wet.
Your hair is wet.
You look like you’re about to give me opinions.//What is it? Spit it out.
Right, the big old scar.
Jeez! I wouldn’t have known if you hadn’t mentioned it. Thanks, Sherlock.

Special.SourceString: You have a giant scar across your face.

Text.SourceString: Ha!//<portrait=angry>Flirting, are you, Garden Rake?//<portrait=annoyed>Thanks. Scars are sexy. That’s why I have one.

Special.SourceString: That scar looks good on you.

Text.SourceString: I got my scar from one of the cats at the shelter. Not from fighting off a bear or a wolf. Not a combat scar, nope!//<portrait=annoyed>I’m far too good to get injured in combat. Heh heh!//<portrait=normal>It’s the one you let your guard down for who hurts you.
My scar might look scary to people, but I’m not too worried about it.//My face is fine. Still functioning as intended.
Poor Chap, the cat that scratched me, didn’t mean it.// I was about to give him his vaccine and he was scared. But he was very brave about it at the end of the day.
I don’t like talking about my scar because first of all, it’s nobody’s business.//<portrait=angry>Second of all, it’s <Italic>still</> nobody’s business.
I don’t live here. This is where I work.//<portrait=angry>Those aren’t my crops. I look like a farmer to ya?
I love the cold. Mmm…invigorating!
I’ve ever stepped foot into Socket Electronics in my life…//<portrait=annoyed>Socket & Pan – yeah, whatever. The electronics store.//I don’t have much use for gadgets.
Saw that duck with the little helmet on my way here…
Name’s Funbucket.
Saw that duck with the little helmet on my way here…//<portrait=happy>It was adorable.

I spoke to <NpcName>Ben</> some time ago. Saw him walking the duck near the cavern. He told me his name was Funbucket.//<portrait=angry>And by “his” I mean the duck’s name, not <NpcName>Ben’s</>. <NpcName>Ben’s</> name is Ben.
It’s quiet tonight, just how I like it.
It’s quiet tonight. A little too quiet.//Stay frosty, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I’m visiting <NPCName>Rafael</> later today.//My sword could use some sharpening.
Gah, it’s Winter. Means he’s busy upgrading farming tools.//<portrait=normal>I’ll wait till Spring.
You’re walking around at this time of day like you got nothing to do.
I’m a little tired today. <NPCName>Paul</> thought he saw the wooded bighorn in the backyard last night, and…//<portrait=annoyed>Let’s just say it was a whole thing. No one got much sleep.
I like the hot cocoa from the Coffee Corner.//Don’t like coffee.
My favorite thing to get from the Coffee Corner is hot cocoa.//Not a fan of coffee. It’s a tad bitter for my taste.
I’m sick of hearing people whine about how they can’t handle a little bit of cold weather.
My dog likes to hang around here somewhere…//He’s probably napping near the clinic right now if he isn’t playing with the kids at school.
This job at the pet shelter doesn’t pay much.
Good thing making a lot of money doesn’t interest me.
I’m here to take care of the shelter.//<portrait=angry>What? Pick up a shovel. Help out.
Gotta make sure the shelter is clean and safe for the animals.//They don’t have anywhere else to go.
Some of the animals at the shelter just wandered here from Hillside or the forest – like Taco, the vineyard’s dog.
Are you looking for animals?
I need to clean all the litter boxes today.
It gets busy in here on the weekend.//There’s a yoga class on Saturdays.
Me? No, thanks. I don’t think I’ll be joining the yoga class anytime soon.
You’re not looking for seeds here, are you?//<portrait=angry>I don’t sell seeds.
If you’re going to keep talking, let me go first…
Why do you look like that? I startled you, huh? Tch.//<portrait=normal>Jumpy farmer, aren’t ya?
Summer’s almost here.//Might need to change up my gear.
I don’t fish much. Don’t need to.
You can fish in that rice field, by the way. It’s free.
I don’t fish much. Don’t need to.//You can fish in that rice field, by the way. It’s free.
That would require you to be <Italic>able</> to fish in the first place.
All the weapons are inside the guild, not here.
We keep weapons inside the B.O.S. guild right there. That little round door by the bush.//It’s safer to keep them all in one place. Easier to maintain as well.
You have animals on your farm?
You feed them all right over there? Let them get some sun sometimes?
Those rotten roots at the beach are nasty.//I tried getting rid of them over there. Cutting them up doesn’t work.
They come back again.//I think the solution might be down on the ocean bed.
It’s nice and hot today.
I like reading books at the beach.//<portrait=angry>I don’t care if people think it’s a cliché.
Not surprising to see you here at the beach in the Summer.
I’m certainly gonna spend my Summer at the beach. Why not?//<portrait=normal>It’s free. It’s fun.
Hot spring is empty this time of year.//Perfect.
Weird that shiitake only grows in Spring here.//It grows in Spring and Fall in Beluga.
The sunscreen they sell around here comes in tiny little bottles.//It barely covers my legs. Tch.//<portrait=angry>What a scam!
Here I thought I was gonna read my book in peace. Tch.
Don’t pass out. The shack sells coconuts.
The ones on the trees aren’t ripe yet. Could be wrong…
Hey! Can’t resist the beach in this weather either, huh?//<portrait=happy>Look at us. The moment the sun shines, we hit the beach. Typical islanders. Tch.
This book is from the library.
I don’t buy books. I prefer to read the free ones.
There’s so many people living on this island.//Wouldn’t know it at first – barely see anybody around.
When I’m at the community center, I just assume most of them are tourists.//<portrait=normal>Except the one doing yoga, Pink Hair. I know she lives here.
I’m feeling a little sore from training the other day.//<portrait=sad>At least now I’m relaxing here on the beach, but it doesn’t seem to help my muscle recovery.
I might need to hit the hot spring on the way home. Just a dip or something.//<portrait=annoyed>This heat? Tch. Doesn’t bother me.
You’re in my way.//I need to see if the shiitake are sprouting yet.
Shiitake are great. Other mushrooms are okay.//Not that good.
I’m gonna be here for a bit.//<portrait=annoyed>Why are you still here?

Didn’t bring anything to eat today. I thought I could just pop by the shack if I get hungry.//It’s right there.//<portrait=annoyed>I did get some coffee this morning. Bad decision. Should’ve gotten the hot cocoa instead.
Here for those yoga classes, are ya?//Pink Hair teaches it. See it all the time.
There’s so many people living on this island.//Wouldn’t know it at first – barely see anybody around.
When I’m at the community center, I just assume most of them are tourists.//<portrait=normal>Except the one doing yoga, Pink Hair. I know she lives here.
You sure are everywhere, Garden Rake.//<portrait=normal>All right, what is it?
The hot water feels good.
I can feel my muscles relaxing.
This place is free.
Heard you had something to do with getting it going again. Is that right?
I’m gonna see if there’s some mushrooms out there. After this. Aaaaah…
